@page "/"

<PageTitle>EasyWoWMacro - World of Warcraft Macro Editor</PageTitle>

<div class="container-fluid">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-12">
            <div class="jumbotron text-center py-5">
                <h1 class="display-4">EasyWoWMacro</h1>
                <p class="lead">Create and edit World of Warcraft macros with validation and a user-friendly interface</p>
                <hr class="my-4">
                <p>Build complex macros with conditionals, validate your syntax, and get instant feedback on your macro structure.</p>
                <a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" href="macro-editor" role="button">Start Creating Macros</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row mt-4">
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <div class="card h-100">
                <div class="card-body text-center">
                    <i class="bi bi-check-circle text-success" style="font-size: 3rem;"></i>
                    <h5 class="card-title mt-3">Real-time Validation</h5>
                    <p class="card-text">Get instant feedback on your macro syntax and structure. Our parser validates commands, conditionals, and arguments against WoW's macro system.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <div class="card h-100">
                <div class="card-body text-center">
                    <i class="bi bi-eye text-info" style="font-size: 3rem;"></i>
                    <h5 class="card-title mt-3">Visual Structure</h5>
                    <p class="card-text">See your macro broken down into its components - directives, commands, conditionals, and arguments - for better understanding and debugging.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <div class="card h-100">
                <div class="card-body text-center">
                    <i class="bi bi-clipboard text-warning" style="font-size: 3rem;"></i>
                    <h5 class="card-title mt-3">Easy Export</h5>
                    <p class="card-text">Copy your validated macro directly to your clipboard with one click, ready to paste into World of Warcraft's macro interface.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row mt-4">
        <div class="col-12">
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-header">
                    <h4>Example Macro</h4>
                </div>
                <div class="card-body">
                    <p>Here's an example of a complex macro that the editor can parse and validate:</p>
                    <pre class="bg-light p-3 rounded"><code>#showtooltip
/cast [@@target,harm,nodead] Smite; [@@target,help,nodead] Flash Heal
/use [combat] Healthstone
/say [combat] Using Healthstone!</code></pre>
                    <p class="mt-3">This macro shows how to use conditionals to cast different spells based on target type, use items in combat, and send chat messages.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
